The article discusses the White House's statement on the awarding of the Nobel Peace Prize to the Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW). President Obama congratulates the OPCW and emphasizes the international community's commitment to prohibiting the use of chemical weapons. The OPCW has been instrumental in eliminating dangerous weapons and is currently working on eliminating Syria's chemical weapons program. The United States strongly supports the OPCW's efforts and calls on all nations to end the Syrian conflict and support the elimination of chemical weapons.